718475f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 75th Street
718475f-a.text:
Central Park West, west side, from 75th to 77th Streets. At the extreme left is the old San Remo, now replaced by a new apartment building with the same name. The next building on the N.W. corner of 75th Street is the Kenilworth, another old apartment house. On the S.W. corner of 76th Street stands the Church of the Divine Paternity (Universalist). The white marble building at the right is the New York Historical Society.
February 2, 1929.
P. L. Sperr, Photographer.
